  "title": "The Twice-Dead King Omnibus",
  "synopsis": "Nate Crowley's complete Twice-Dead King in one volume: the duology Ruin and Reign — exiled lord Oltyx's reckoning with the brother who broke him, the orks at his gates, and the flayer curse rotting his own court from within — together with the novella Severed and a clutch of shorter pieces that fill out the same dynasty's long, weary history. Read end to end, the omnibus traces a kind of necron tragedy: a species that traded life for immortality and now spends eternity defending the bargain it made, told through one disgraced lord who is slowly remembering what was taken from him. A natural entry point for readers who want the whole arc — court intrigue, crownworld siege, fleet exodus — in a single doorstopper.",
